<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911007-0009</DOCNO><DOCID>911007-0009.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sterling Optical Corp.:   Wider Loss at $37.7 Million   Is Estimated for Fiscal 1991</HL><DATE>10/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   EYE</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>SPECIALTY RETAILERS OF LIMITED PRODUCT LINES (OTS)ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Sterling Optical Corp. said preliminary fiscal 1991figures indicate that its net loss widened to $37.7 million,or $7.42 a share, after restructuring charges and losses fromdiscontinued operations.   The operator of a chain of optical stores added that it isselling 11 of its stores in New York and New Jersey to acompany it didn't identify. Sterling operates 215 retailstores, 118 of which are franchised or licensed, primarily inthe Northeast.</LP><TEXT>   Sterling Optical, based in Hackensack, N.J., said theestimates for the fiscal year ended June 30 includerestructuring charges of about $16 million, or $3.16 a share,and losses from disposal of discontinued operations of about$2.1 million, or 41 cents a share. Company-owned store salesare estimated at about $72.7 million.   For fiscal 1990, Sterling had a loss of $8.4 million, or$1.67 a share, after restructuring charges of $8.8 million,or $1.73 a share; profit from discontinued operations of $2.4million, or 47 cents a share; and an extraordinary gain of$2.2 million, or 44 cents a share. Company-owned store saleswere $87.9 million.   The company said it expects final fiscal 1991 figures tobe available within two weeks.</TEXT></DOC>